SIMPLE: impersonate
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Impersonate
<hw>Im*per"son*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Impersonated</conjf>
<pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Impersonating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To invest with
personality; to endow with the form of a living being.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To ascribe the qualities of a person to; to
personify.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To assume, or to represent, the person or character
of; to personate; <as>as, he <ex>impersonated</ex>
Macbeth</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Benedict <qex>impersonated</qex> his age.</q>
<rj><qau>Milman.</qau></rj></p>

<p><ent>Impersonification</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Impersonation</ent>⟦br⟧
